seems pretty right wing to me from what i can tell by the reviews on this page , all the proposals in this book are basically libertarian . it is thus highly misleading that the book calls itself centrist . the fact that only one person on this page has realized this , yet seems to think it 's a good thing , is also rather disturbing . the book seems like a thinly veiled attempt to move political dialogue rightward by making radical neoconservative proposals -- many of which the bush administration clearly supports -- seem moderate . let 's call a spade a spade